      "role": "user",
      "content": "i guess. but it's hard to see it as just \"letting go of pressure.\" it feels more like everyone would just be lighter. like the air would be a little cleaner if there wasn't this... emptiness dragging things down. it feels more like an exit than an ending. why is it so much harder for people to accept that some things are just better off when they're gone?",
